d.title: User can create a UTM template with only whitespace characters in the name and UTM parameters
d.body: ### Issue Summary Users are currently able to create UTM templates where the name and UTM parameters consist only of whitespace characters. This results in templates that appear blank, which can lead to confusion when reviewing or editing them. ### Steps to Reproduce 1. Navigate to the UTM template creation page: [https://app.dub.co/\/settings/library/tags](https://app.dub.co//settings/library/tags) 2. Enter only whitespace characters in the "Name" field. 3. Enter only whitespace characters in one or more of the UTM parameter fields (e.g., utm_source, utm_medium, etc.). 4. Save the template. ### Expected behavior Following Dub's design convention, creating a template with only whitespace characters should be prevented. This may include showing an error message or an error toast. The assignee should clarify this with the core team before they start coding. ### Reproduction / Screenshots https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f0143359-0cdf-4763-a7ec-1133e9ecd151

d.title: Error: `DEFAULT value is not allowed when jsonpath is set` when running Dub.co's pipe
d.body: ### Issue Summary While following [the guide to run Dub.co’s codebase locally](https://dub.co/docs/local-development#step-2-set-up-tinybird-clickhouse-database), I encountered an error when executing `tb push`. The error message indicates that when you specify a column with a jsonpath attribute, you cannot also provide a DEFAULT value for that column. The error is caused by 4 files: 1. `dub_lead_events.datasource` 2. `dub_links_metadata.datasource` 3. `dub_sale_events.datasource` 4. `dub_webhook_events.datasource` ### Steps to Reproduce 1. Follow the setup instructions provided in the guide up to [Step 2: Set up the Tinybird Clickhouse database](https://dub.co/docs/local-development#step-2-set-up-tinybird-clickhouse-database). 5. After you run `tb push`, wait for the command to fail and observe the error message like on the screenshot below. ### Expected behavior The command should execute successfully, creating the essential data sources without errors. ### Screenshots ### Version info - Tinybird CLI Version 2.0.0 (rev 40c7bee) - macOS Version 13.5.2 (22G91)

d.title: [Bug]: search does not return expected destinations / results
d.body: Hi @steven-tey, I shared this issue with you via E-Mail, but this could also be of interest as an issue in the official repo. Here is an example I'm talking about: I've looked up the following string `http://localhost:3010/hotel/011428dc-45c2` (the string I am interested in is even longer with query params), and I get results like this: The app's request looks like this: `https://app.dub.co/api/links?search=http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3010%2Fhotel%2F011428dc-45c2&showArchived=true&slug=xxx` This makes e.g. validating if destinations already exist (with the API) before creating new links impossible. ## Related Code https://github.com/steven-tey/dub/blob/a2a4f43eb5f606eb159a59e882418aefdbee9264/lib/api/links.ts#L30-L61 Edit: Well, what a coincidence, this is Issue #404! 😅 🤣

d.title: Black background on the record  when we hover bar graph.
d.body: The black background and dark grey colour make it difficult to see the records. ## Steps to reproduce. 1. Open any of your shorten links created with dub.sh. 2. Open analytics for that link. 3. Hover over the bar graph.

d.title: fix(api): reorder `trim()` method calls in Zod schema
d.body:
## What does this PR do?

- [x] Moves `trim()` method to be called before `min(1)` to resolve validation issues.
- [x] Adds `trim()` to all UTM fields in UTM Create schema.

Fixes: #1647

## How to test?

Make sure that creating a UTM template with only whitespace characters is prevented. You should see "UTM name is required" error toast.

d.title: Issues with short linking twitter profiles/tweets
d.body:
Good day to you all here,

There seems to be an issue when linking to twitter, it produces a "**Too Many Redirects**" error when using the non-self-hosted version of Dub.

My "setup" is using a custom domain which uses Cloudflare for DNS/protection

Thing's I've tried:

- Disable caching in Cloudflare - didn't work
- Disabling Cloudflare completely - didn't work
- Change domains in Dub - didn't work
- Check if twitter can even be short linked using another service(bit.ly) - it works there
